This paper discusses the development of value alignment systems in AI, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the interrelation between ethical reasoning and empirical observation, which could be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper touches on the topic of cybersecurity (cs.CY) as it discusses the potential problems with AI training routines. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of ethical principles, which could be relevant to cryptography (cs.CR) as it involves the study of secure communication and information.
